  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver pipeline involves multi-threaded parallel execution, adaptive mesh refinement routines, and a hemolysis transport sub-model implemented as a user-defined function (UDF). Solver robustness was studied informally during development; no systematic fault-injection, convergence-failure, or NaN-propagation testing was conducted.",
